profile_positions.description:
Freelance consultant.  I have been doing several consultancies, including:
–	providing training, planning and organizational support to the United Nations Institute for Training and Research (UNITAR) within three projects on chemicals and waste (a project on open burning of waste in the SADC region, a project on the internet-based Toolbox for Decision Making in Chemicals Management prepared by the IOMC (The Inter-Organization Programme for the Sound Management of Chemicals), and a project on sound management of chemicals and waste in Nigeria);
–	conducting the mid-term review (as international team leader) of the GEF FAO project “Lifecycle Management of Pesticides and Disposal of POPs Pesticides in Central Asian Countries and Turkey”; 
–	conducting the mid-term review of the GEF FAO project “Pesticide Risk Reduction in Bangladesh”;
–	conducting the terminal evaluations for the UNEP Evaluation Office of the following projects:
o	UNEP GEF project “Development of a Plan for Global Monitoring of Human Exposure to and Environmental Concentrations of Mercury”;
o	UNEP GEF project “Demonstrating Cost-effectiveness and Sustainability of Environmentally Sound and Locally Appropriate Alternatives to DDT for Malaria Vector Control in Africa”;
o	three global waste projects implemented by UNEP IETC (International Environmental Technology Centre);
–	supporting the UN ITU (International Telecommunications Union) with preparation of a programme on e-waste;
–	providing expertise as Obsolete Pesticides and Environmental Remediation Advisor in Central Asia for FSD (Swiss Foundation for Mine Action);
–	providing support to the CWCC (Chemicals Weapons Convention Coalition) to ensure participation of civil society organisations at the annual Conference of the State Parties of the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) in The Hague.

(Senior) Project manager at Milieukontakt International (formerly Milieukontakt Oost-Europa).
Involved in projects in Albania, Armenia, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Bulgaria, Georgia, Kyrgyzstan, Macedonia, Moldova, Mongolia, Tajikistan, Ukraine and Romania related to: 
–	Elimination of health and environmental risks from POPs and obsolete pesticides;
–	Public Participation and awareness raising on environmental and health topics for vulnerable groups;
–	Green Agenda (methodology for local sustainable development);
–	Capacity building and network development of (environmental and health) CSOs and other stakeholder groups;

Tasks performed:
–	Set-up and coordination of projects (including regular field visits);
–	Coordination of project offices abroad;
–	Acquisition of projects and preparation of project proposals and budgets;
–	Maintaining, supporting and extending of (CSO) networks in project countries;
–	Responsible for financial and contract management of projects;
–	Internal and external Monitoring & Evaluation;
–	Conducting trainings (mostly on Awareness Raising on Obsolete Pesticides, Public Participation, Result Based Programming and Green Agenda);
–	Communication on projects, writing and editing of news items and articles for project websites and newsletters;
–	Organization of and reporting on conferences, meetings and seminars.

Intermediary at an employment agency for municipal institutions in Amsterdam.

	Tasks performed:
–	Deployment of staff to municipal institutions;
–	Conducting intake, performance and assessment interviews;
–	Responsible for maintaining relations with several municipal institutions and museums; 
–	Responsible for returns and results of the work unit.

Project manager at Top Trade Matching, Groningen, responsible for contacts in Russia and the Baltic States.
Top Trade Matching was the follow-up of Project Matching, and an initiative of ING, KPMG and Small Business Centre in Groningen. The aim of this initiative was to establish business contacts between small and medium sized companies in the North of the Netherlands and Central and Eastern Europe. 

	Tasks performed: 
–	Making international market analyses, competitor’s analyses, investigating market access possibilities and performing feasibility studies;
–	Meeting potential business partners in Russia and the Baltic States;
–	Interpretation and translation tasks (Russian-English/English-Russian and Russian-Dutch/Dutch-Russian) during contacts between companies in the North of the Netherlands and companies in Russia or the Baltic States.
